# Parallel Test Runner - Elixir Target (EXPERIMENTAL)
# 
# This is an EXPERIMENTAL version that compiles the ParallelTestRunner to Elixir!
# This serves as both:
# 1. A real-world stress test of the Elixir compilation target
# 2. A performance comparison vs interpreter version
# 3. Validation that our compiler can handle complex tooling
#
# Features being tested:
# - sys.io.Process → Elixir Port/System.cmd
# - File system operations → Elixir File module  
# - JSON parsing → Jason library integration
# - Complex control flow and state management
# - Command line argument parsing
#
# Usage:
#   haxe test/ParallelTestElixir.hxml            # Compile to Elixir
#   mix run lib/ParallelTestRunner.ex -j 4       # Run compiled version
#   
# Performance comparison:
#   time haxe test/ParallelTest.hxml             # Interpreter version
#   time mix run lib/ParallelTestRunner.ex       # Compiled Elixir version

# Main class
-main test.ParallelTestRunner

# Class paths
-cp test
-cp src
-cp std

# Target: Elixir (EXPERIMENTAL - this is dogfooding!)
-lib reflaxe.elixir

# Output directory for generated Elixir code
-D elixir_output=lib/test_runner

# Generate executable script
-D generate_main=true